AI/LLM ENGINEER – python  
Responsibilities:  
• Developing and fine-tuning AI models, including large language models (LLMs). • Implementing and optimizing deep learning architectures for NLP, computer vision, and generative 
AI applications. • Training models using frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, or JAX. • Utilizing APIs from platforms like OpenAI, Gemini (Google), Cohere, or Hugging Face for LLM 
deployment. • Designing and implementing retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines for better AI 
responses. • Building and maintaining vector databases such as FAISS, ChromaDB, or Weaviate. • Preprocessing and cleaning large datasets for AI model training. • Developing and deploying AI-powered applications using FastAPI, Flask, or similar backend 
frameworks. • Optimizing model inference for efficiency and scalability in production environments. • Implementing prompt engineering techniques to refine model outputs. • Conducting research to improve AI/ML models and applying state-of-the-art methodologies. • Monitoring model performance, debugging issues, and fine-tuning hyperparameters. • Working with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure) for model training and deployment. Requirements  
• 1.5+ years of experience in AI/ML development, with a focus on LLMs. • Strong proficiency in Python and experience with libraries like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Hugging 
Face Transformers. • Familiarity with retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) and vector databases. • Knowledge of NLP techniques, including tokenization, embeddings, and transformers. • Experience using APIs from OpenAI, Google Gemini, Cohere, or similar providers. • Understanding of model fine-tuning, zero-shot, and few-shot learning techniques. • Hands-on experience with LangChain or LlamaIndex for LLM-powered applications. • Experience deploying AI models using Docker and Kubernetes. • Proficiency in data wrangling, feature engineering, and model evaluation. • Knowledge of cloud-based AI/ML services like AWS SageMaker, Vertex AI, or Azure ML. • Strong problem-solving skills and ability to optimize AI solutions for real-world applications. Nice to Have: 
• Experience with reinforcement learning (RLHF) for AI model improvement. • Understanding of multi-modal AI models (text, image, and speech). • Familiarity with edge AI and deploying models on low-power devices. • Experience with MLOps tools like MLflow, Prefect, or Kubeflow. • Research experience in AI, with publications in NLP, generative AI, or deep learning.

Data Science and Analytics – Python, SQL  
Responsibilities:  
• Collecting, cleaning, and preprocessing large datasets for analysis. • Performing exploratory data analysis (EDA) to uncover insights and patterns. • Building and evaluating machine learning models using Python and scikit-learn. • Developing statistical models to support decision-making and business intelligence. • Implementing feature engineering techniques to improve model accuracy. • Visualizing data using libraries like Matplotlib, Seaborn, and Plotly. • Writing and optimizing SQL queries for data extraction and manipulation. • Communicating findings and presenting insights through reports and dashboards. • Automating data workflows and pipelines for efficiency. • Collaborating with cross-functional teams to drive data-driven strategies. • Keeping up to date with the latest trends in data science, AI, and machine learning. Requirements  
• 1.5+ years of experience in data analysis and machine learning. • Proficiency in Python and data analysis libraries (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn). • Understanding of machine learning algorithms (regression, classification, clustering). • Experience with model training, evaluation, and hyperparameter tuning. • Strong knowledge of data preprocessing and feature engineering. • Hands-on experience with data visualization tools (Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly). • Ability to perform statistical analysis and hypothesis testing. • Familiarity with SQL for querying relational databases. • Experience with Jupyter Notebook, Google Colab, or other development environments. • Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail. • Ability to translate business problems into data-driven solutions. • Excellent communication and reporting skills. Nice to Have: 
• Experience with deep learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch). • Knowledge of MLOps, model deployment, and cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure). • Experience working with big data technologies (Spark, Hadoop). • Familiarity with business intelligence tools (Power BI, Tableau, Looker). PROJECT MANAGER  
Responsibilities:  
• Overseeing the recruitment process, including sourcing, interviewing, and hiring candidates. • Managing employee onboarding, training, and professional development programs. • Developing and implementing HR policies, procedures, and compliance measures. • Handling employee relations, conflict resolution, and workplace grievances. • Maintaining and updating employee records, contracts, and performance evaluations. • Coordinating payroll, benefits administration, and compensation structures. • Ensuring compliance with labor laws, regulations, and company policies. • Conducting performance appraisals and providing feedback to employees. • Organizing team-building activities, wellness programs, and company culture initiatives. • Supporting workforce planning and talent management strategies. • Managing diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) initiatives. • Monitoring and improving employee engagement, retention, and satisfaction. Requirements  
• 2+ years of experience in human resources or a related role. • Strong understanding of HR policies, labor laws, and compliance regulations. • Experience with recruitment, hiring, and talent acquisition strategies. • Proficiency in HR management software (e.g., BambooHR, Workday, SAP SuccessFactors). • Excellent communication, leadership, and conflict-resolution skills. • Strong organizational and time-management abilities. • Ability to handle confidential information with integrity and discretion. • Knowledge of employee benefits, payroll processing, and compensation structures. • Familiarity with performance management, training, and development programs. Nice to Have: 
• HR certifications such as SHRM-CP, PHR, or CIPD. • Experience with remote workforce management and hybrid work models. • Understanding of HR analytics, employee engagement tools, and workforce planning. • Background in diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) initiatives.

Mobile Development – Flutter  
Responsibilities:  
• Developing cross-platform applications for iOS and Android using Flutter. • Designing and implementing user-friendly UI/UX with smooth animations and transitions. • Writing clean, maintainable, and efficient Dart code. • Ensuring high performance and responsiveness of applications. • Integrating RESTful APIs and third-party services. • Implementing state management solutions (Provider, Riverpod, Bloc, GetX, etc.). • Troubleshooting UI/UX inconsistencies and fixing bugs. • Optimizing apps for performance and scalability. • Writing unit and integration tests to ensure application stability. • Working with Firebase for authentication, real-time database, push notifications, and analytics. • Collaborating with UI/UX designers, backend developers, and stakeholders to deliver high-quality 
mobile applications. • Keeping up with Flutter updates, best practices, and new technologies. Requirements  
• 1.5+ years of experience working with Flutter and Dart. • Strong knowledge of mobile architecture and best practices. • Experience with state management (Provider, Bloc, GetX, etc.). • Familiarity with RESTful APIs and third-party integrations. • Experience with Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Cloud Messaging, etc.). • Knowledge of UI/UX principles and ability to create responsive designs. • Understanding of platform differences (iOS vs. Android) and how to handle them in Flutter. • Experience in publishing apps to Google Play Store and Apple App Store. • Strong debugging and performance optimization skills. • Familiarity with Git version control and CI/CD for mobile development. • Good understanding of asynchronous programming and Dart Futures/Streams. • Ability to write unit and integration tests to ensure app reliability. • Excellent problem-solving and communication skills. Nice to Have: 
• Experience with native Android (Kotlin) or iOS (Swift) for platform-specific integrations. • Familiarity with GraphQL or WebSockets. • Knowledge of Docker and DevOps for mobile.

PROJECT MANAGER  
Responsibilities:  
• Overseeing project planning, execution, and completion within scope, budget, and timeline. • Defining project goals, objectives, deliverables, and success criteria. • Coordinating with cross-functional teams, including developers, designers, and stakeholders. • Developing and managing project schedules, resource allocation, and risk assessments. • Tracking project progress using Agile, Scrum, or Waterfall methodologies. • Facilitating team meetings, stand-ups, sprint planning, and retrospectives. • Identifying and mitigating risks to ensure project success. • Communicating project updates to stakeholders, clients, and executives. • Ensuring deliverables meet quality standards and client expectations. • Managing project documentation, reports, and post-mortem analysis. • Handling change management and resolving project roadblocks. • Collaborating with business analysts to align projects with company objectives. Requirements  
• 2+ years of experience in project management, preferably in tech or software development. • Strong understanding of Agile, Scrum, Kanban, or Waterfall methodologies. • Proficiency in project management tools like Jira, Trello, Asana, or ClickUp. • Excellent leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills. • Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and prioritize tasks effectively. • Strong problem-solving and risk management capabilities. • Experience with budget planning and resource allocation. • Familiarity with software development processes and technical team collaboration. • Ability to create and interpret project reports, Gantt charts, and progress dashboards. Nice to Have: 
• Certification in PMP, PRINCE2, or Certified Scrum Master (CSM). • Experience working in SaaS, AI, fintech, or health tech industries. • Understanding of UX/UI principles and software development life cycle (SDLC). • Background in data-driven decision-making and performance tracking.
